  "description": "<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p742116/\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_shuangyu.gif\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a><br /><p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201508/fc9c1b84c24649c385b549bf3c6cced6.jpg\" style=\"height: 330px; width: 440px;\" /></p>\n<p>\n\tNOTE: Any spell-check program ought to catch most of these for you. However, the wisest course is to master them yourself.注意：任何拼写检查程序都应该能发现其中大部分错误。但最明智的做法是自己掌握它们。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">For fun, I did a search for the incorrect version of nine of the ten. I didn&rsquo;t bother with Number 7 because both&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">its </em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">and&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">it&rsquo;s</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;are valid spellings. The number of hits for the misspellings is shown in parentheses. Some refer to intentional misspellings on English sites like this one, but not all.</span>出于乐趣，我搜索了10个错误拼写中的9个。我没有搜第7个是因为its和it&rsquo;s都是正确的拼写。括号中是错误拼写的搜索结果数。其中部分错误是像这个网站中出现的那样，属于有目的的拼写错误，但并非所有都如此。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">1.&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">argument </strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;arguement&rdquo; 730,000)</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The verb is&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">argue</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">, but the noun is&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">argument</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">.</span>动词是argue，但名词是argument。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">2. </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">calendar </strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;calender&rdquo; 29,600,000)&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The register on which you schedule your appointments is spelled&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">calendar</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. Yes, there is a specialized term spelled&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">calender</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;that refers to paper production, but I doubt that it accounts for millions of uses.</span>用来记录约会的登记簿拼作calendar。的确，有一个拼作calender（意思是砑光机）的造纸行业术语，但我怀疑数以百万计搜索结果恐怕不会都来自这么偏僻的单词。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">3. </span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/cemetery\" target=\"_blank\">cemetery</a><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;cemetary&rdquo;185,000,000)</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">There are three&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">e</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&rsquo;s in&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">cemetery</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. Nary an&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">a</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;in sight.</span>Cemetery中有3个e，没有a。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">4. </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">definite </strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;definate&rdquo; 539,000)</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Think,&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">finite</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">,&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">infinite</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">,&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">infinity</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. Look at all those&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">i</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&rsquo;s. No&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">a</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&rsquo;s anywhere in&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">definite</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">.</span>想想finite、infinite和infinity。看看这些i。Definite里没有a。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">5. </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">finally </strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;finaly&rdquo; 1,450,000)</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The adjective is&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">final</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. The adverb is&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">finally</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. Double that&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">l</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;in&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">finally</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. </span>形容词是final，副词是finally。L要写两遍。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">6. </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">forty </strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;fourty&rdquo; 783,000)&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">One less than five is spelled&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">four</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. One more than thirty-nine is spelled&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">forty</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. </span>5 &ndash; 1 = 4（four），39 + 1 = 40（forty）。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">7. </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">its</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;(possessive adjective)</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The problem with this habitual misspelling is that both&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">its</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">it&rsquo;s</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;are English spellings.&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">It&rsquo;s</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;is a contraction of the words &ldquo;It is.&rdquo;&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Its</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;is a possessive adjective, like&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">his</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. The best advice is to spell out &ldquo;it is&rdquo; when that is your meaning. You cannot rely on grammar/spell checkers to catch this one. Indeed, Word often advises me to write &ldquo;it&rsquo;s&rdquo; when the context calls for&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">its</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">.</span>对于这个经常拼错的单词，问题在于its和it&rsquo;s都是英语中正确的拼写。It&rsquo;s是it is的缩写。像his一样，its则是所有格形容词。最好的建议是当你想用it&rsquo;s时把它写成it is。你不能依赖语法或拼写检查程序来发现这个错误。事实上，Word经常在文中应该出现its的时候建议我写it&rsquo;s。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">8. </span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">separate </strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;seperate&rdquo; 31,700,000)&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">Take the word by syllables:&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">sep-a-rate</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. Yes, we pronounce it [sep-uh-ret], but we spell it&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">sep-a-rate</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. Look for &ldquo;a rat&rdquo; in sep.a.rat.e.</span>把这个词按音节划分：sep-a-rate。我们的确把它读为[sep-uh-ret]，但拼写则是sep-a-rate。在separate中有只老鼠（a rat）。</p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">9. </span><a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/tragedy\" target=\"_blank\">tragedy</a><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;tradgedy&rdquo; 212,000)</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">g</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;in&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">tragedy</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;is soft. The&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">e</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;makes the&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">g</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">&nbsp;soft. No extra&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">d</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">, please.</span>Tragedy中的g发软辅音，e让g发软辅音。请不要多加d。<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">小编注：g发硬辅音时，念作[g]，例如go；发软辅音时，念作[dʒ]，例如gym。</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">10.&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">truly</strong><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">(&ldquo;truely&rdquo; 62,600,000)&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">The adjective is&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">true</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">. The adverb is&nbsp;</span><em style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">truly</em><span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">.</span>形容词是true。副词是truly。</p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2000007629395px;\">\n\t原文链接：<a href=\"http://www.dailywritingtips.com/10-misspelled-words-that-get-me-down/\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.dailywritingtips.com/10-misspelled-words-that-get-me-down/</a></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2000007629395px;\">\n\t<a href=\"http://www.dailywritingtips.com/\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201507/9201ef5680f84520a6348b4b10841898.png\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 25.2000007629395px;\">\n\t<span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.8em;\">Daily Writing Tips是由数位英美写作专家维护的博客。</span><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.8em;\">每日更新文章,介绍从语法到词汇应用等英语知识。沪江英语获得翻译和发布授权，请勿转载。</span></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p742116/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p742116\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p741655/\">喝完可乐的一小时 你所发生的变化</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p741659/\">八一建军节：欧美大片里穿军装的男神们</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a 